From: Psygreg <psygreg@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 11 Nov 2025 22:53:18 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] bore-cachy: add missing variable declarations for compilation fix

Add the necessary variable declarations (sysctl_sched_min_base_slice and
nsecs_per_tick) to fix kernel compilation issues with the BORE scheduler.

Signed-off-by: Psygreg <psygreg@pm.me>
---
 kernel/sched/core.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/core.c b/kernel/sched/core.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/core.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/core.c
@@ -206,8 +206,11 @@ static inline void update_load_set(struct load_weight *lw, unsigned long w)
  *
  * This idea comes from the SD scheduler of Con Kolivas:
  */
 #ifdef CONFIG_SCHED_BORE
+unsigned int sysctl_sched_min_base_slice = CONFIG_MIN_BASE_SLICE_NS;
 static void update_sysctl(void) {
+	const unsigned int nsecs_per_tick = 1000000000ULL / HZ;
 	sysctl_sched_base_slice = nsecs_per_tick *
 		max(1UL, DIV_ROUND_UP(sysctl_sched_min_base_slice, nsecs_per_tick));
 }
 void sched_update_min_base_slice(void) { update_sysctl(); }